  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/3916",
  "title": "feat(defer): implement cancellable callback",
  "body": "This PR adds a method `cancel` on a deferred function. We'll use it inside the `dispose` method of `InstantSearch` to prevent scheduled render to happen on an instance that is already disposed. Here is an example of its usage:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst fn1 = defer(() => {\r\n  console.log('Hello');\r\n});\r\n\r\nconst fn2 = defer(() => {\r\n  console.log('Bye');\r\n});\r\n\r\nfn1();\r\nfn2();\r\n\r\nfn1.cancel();\r\n\r\nconsole.log('Start');\r\nPromise.resolve().then(() => {\r\n  console.log('Done');\r\n});\r\n\r\n// Output:\r\n// Start\r\n// Bye\r\n// Done\r\n```\r\n",
